I remembered seeing these growing up. I was curious how it was and why it was disappearing, so I grabbed one. First off, this is not the worst sub I have ever had. It's just like, really really far from the best too. It's just like they bought "the good brand" of everything (packaged meat, packaged bread, cheese ect). And that's it. Nothing special. The bread was fresh like a loaf of bread from Walmart. I really feel like they were just skimpy with everything. $10 for a sandwhich that at it's thickest point 5 paper thin slices of meat each. And then on top of that, you want to charge me an extra dollar for wanting more pickles than 8 paper thin slices. I guess I get why they are disappearing. Everything is just very plain. You can find a better sub shop on almost every corner of nyc.
